  "text": "In the example scripts, tw [CITATION_1] and tw [CITATION_2] are used to define the track and push waveforms respectively. The transmit frequencies are found in the first variable of the vector tw.parameters. For the Verasonics L7-4 example script, the transmit frequency of both push and track is set to the center frequency of the transducer, which is 5.2 MHz for the L7-4 transducer. In our C5-2 script, the track frequency is set to 3.1 MHz, which is the center frequency of the C5-2 transducer. The push frequency is set to 2.4 MHz, which is at the lower edge of the -6dB bandwidth. This frequency was determined by measuring the impulse response of the transducer.",
